`app.js` is a minimal 23-line Express.js application exposing two endpoints: `GET /health` and `GET /users`. It's a small demo/stub, not a production application — and the header comment even identifies it as scaffolding ("Simple application for agent to work on").

Given that scope, most OWASP Top 10 categories simply don't apply (no database, no auth, no user input processing, no file handling, no deserialization, no templating). I want to be straightforward rather than invent vulnerabilities that aren't there. Below are the real issues I found, plus hardening recommendations for when this grows.

