## 5. No rate limiting (A04: Insecure Design / A07: Identification & Auth Failures)

Even unauthenticated endpoints like `/health` are DoS targets. Add `express-rate-limit`:

```js
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 100 }));
```

---

## 6. No CORS policy (A05)

Browsers will apply their default same-origin policy, but if you ever add `cors()` without options it defaults to `*`. Be explicit:

```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: ['https://yourapp.example.com'], credentials: true }));
```

