`app.listen(3000)` binds `0.0.0.0` by default. If this is meant to sit behind a reverse proxy, that's fine — but the app should `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` so rate-limiting and logging see real client IPs. If it's exposed directly, terminate TLS (e.g., `https.createServer` or a fronting proxy like nginx/Caddy).

### 7. A08 — No body-size limits (future-proofing)
