## Scope and Overall Assessment

The file is a 23-line Express server exposing two GET endpoints (`/health`, `/users`) plus a listener on port 3000. The application is **small and currently has a limited attack surface** — there is no database, no user-supplied input being processed, no authentication, no file I/O, and no request-body parsing. That said, several defensive hardening gaps exist, and the code will become dangerous the moment it is extended. Below I walk through each OWASP Top 10 (2021) category against the actual code.

