const pinoHttp = require('pino-http');
const logger = pino({ redact: ['req.headers.authorization'] });
app.use(pinoHttp({ logger }));
```

---

### 10. A10 — Server-Side Request Forgery 🟢 N/A

**Issue:** No outbound HTTP calls present. Nothing to flag today. Revisit if you add webhook / URL-fetching features — use allow-lists, not deny-lists.

