| Severity | Count | Items |
|----------|-------|-------|
| Critical | 0 | — |
| High     | 0 | — |
| Medium   | 1 | Missing rate limiting |
| Low      | 4 | No security headers, no CORS policy, no logging/error handler, plain HTTP |
| Info     | 2 | Future-auth on `/users`, input-validation posture |

**Bottom line:** `app.js` has no exploitable injection, authZ, or auth vulnerabilities today because it processes no user input and serves only static demo data. The real gaps are *defense-in-depth hardening* (headers, rate limiting, logging, graceful shutdown) that should be in place before this code accepts any real input or data.

