## Summary

The application is minimal (two GET endpoints returning static data), so the attack surface is small. There are **no injection sinks, no authentication flows, and no user-controlled inputs** being processed, which eliminates most of the critical OWASP Top 10 categories in their current form. That said, there are several hardening issues and latent risks worth addressing before this grows.

