**Severity:** Medium

The app does not set common defensive headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, HSTS, Referrer-Policy). Express sends `X-Powered-By: Express` by default, which leaks framework info.

**Recommendation:** Add `helmet`.
```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.disable('x-powered-by');
app.use(helmet());
```

### 2. No Rate Limiting (OWASP A04 – Insecure Design / DoS)
**Severity:** Medium

Both endpoints are unauthenticated and unthrottled — trivially abusable for DoS or scraping `/users`.

**Recommendation:**
```js
